when you retain it

00:39:44.510 --> 00:39:49.040 align:middle line:84%
and you use it with regard
to attaining your mission.

00:39:49.040 --> 00:39:50.750 align:middle line:84%
I talked about 10
different plays

00:39:50.750 --> 00:39:52.940 align:middle line:84%
in the book, plays
or methods to be

00:39:52.940 --> 00:39:56.960 align:middle line:84%
able to make behavioral
modifications.

00:39:56.960 --> 00:39:59.450 align:middle line:84%
One of those plays
is self-coaching.

00:39:59.450 --> 00:40:02.820 align:middle line:84%
Some people might
be sharp enough

00:40:02.820 --> 00:40:04.820 align:middle line:84%
to be able to make those
behavioral changes just

00:40:04.820 --> 00:40:08.170 align:middle line:84%
by coaching yourself
and saying, OK, Tom.

00:40:08.170 --> 00:40:09.170 align:middle line:90%
You're ready to do this.

00:40:09.170 --> 00:40:10.483 align:middle line:90%
Don't do it.

00:40:10.483 --> 00:40:11.900 align:middle line:84%
That's something
you want to drop.

00:40:11.900 --> 00:40:12.817 align:middle line:90%
You're ready to do it.

00:40:12.817 --> 00:40:14.420 align:middle line:90%
Don't, don't, don't.

00:40:14.420 --> 00:40:16.770 align:middle line:90%
So you can coach yourself.

00:40:16.770 --> 00:40:18.360 align:middle line:90%
That's one option.

00:40:18.360 --> 00:40:24.560 align:middle line:84%
Another option is
that of books, tapes.

00:40:24.560 --> 00:40:29.015 align:middle line:84%
Another option is that of
what I call one-on-one.

00:40:29.015 --> 00:40:33.650 align:middle line:84%
One-on-one is a
great therapist to be

00:40:33.650 --> 00:40:38.760 align:middle line:84%
able to help move
me through these,

00:40:38.760 --> 00:40:44.280 align:middle line:84%
and facilitate team to
assist in the dropping

00:40:44.280 --> 00:40:46.060 align:middle line:90%
of these behaviors.

00:40:46.060 --> 00:40:49.730 align:middle line:84%
The identification of them
and the dropping of them,

00:40:49.730 --> 00:40:51.120 align:middle line:90%
or modifying.

00:40:51.120 --> 00:40:54.270 align:middle line:84%
So that's another
excellent, excellent way.

00:40:54.270 --> 00:40:57.150 align:middle line:84%
Then group therapy was another
important trait for me,

00:40:57.150 --> 00:41:00.150 align:middle line:90%
or another play that helped me.

00:41:00.150 --> 00:41:02.943 align:middle line:84%
The group was
important because--

00:41:02.943 --> 00:41:04.860 align:middle line:84%
the one-on-one was great,
but the group really

00:41:04.860 --> 00:41:06.630 align:middle line:90%
complemented it.

00:41:06.630 --> 00:41:09.460 align:middle line:84%
And then there
were retreats where

00:41:09.460 --> 00:41:11.850 align:middle line:84%
we'd go on a one-week
retreat where

00:41:11.850 --> 00:41:15.000 align:middle line:84%
we're practicing these
behaviors in a full week,

00:41:15.000 --> 00:41:17.530 align:middle line:90%
stumbling here, stumbling there.

00:41:17.530 --> 00:41:22.090 align:middle line:10%
So those are some of the ways
in terms of psychological.

00:41:22.090 --> 00:41:23.860 align:middle line:10%
Spiritual wellness.

00:41:23.860 --> 00:41:26.850 align:middle line:10%
There are many ways for
spiritual practice we all know.

00:41:26.850 --> 00:41:28.440 align:middle line:90%
Prayer, meditation.

00:41:28.440 --> 00:41:31.810 align:middle line:90%
I meditate half an hour a day.

00:41:31.810 --> 00:41:37.700 align:middle line:84%
And I also do what I call
affirmations that are sutras.

00:41:37.700 --> 00:41:41.640 align:middle line:84%
And I learned it
from Deepak, where

00:41:41.640 --> 00:41:45.480 align:middle line:84%
they are various one-word
affirmations that

00:41:45.480 --> 00:41:47.210 align:middle line:90%
line up four per chakra.

00:41:47.210 --> 00:41:48.660 align:middle line:90%
So there's 28 of them.

00:41:48.660 --> 00:41:51.870 align:middle line:84%
So that's been a powerful,
powerful situation,

00:41:51.870 --> 00:41:56.400 align:middle line:84%
are those one-word sutras
which line up with each chakra.

00:41:56.400 --> 00:42:03.810 align:middle line:84%
For instance, the root chakra
is stability, flexibility,

00:42:03.810 --> 00:42:07.750 align:middle line:90%
coherence, and transformation.

00:42:07.750 --> 00:42:10.180 align:middle line:84%
So there's the four
that I say to myself,

00:42:10.180 --> 00:42:13.570 align:middle line:84%
and aim the consciousness
into that area.

00:42:13.570 --> 00:42:20.220 align:middle line:84%
For the crown, it's infinity,
immortality, enlightenment,

00:42:20.220 --> 00:42:21.470 align:middle line:90%
and holy.

00:42:21.470 --> 00:42:26.240 align:middle line:84%
So I get real power out of
that when I say those words

00:42:26.240 --> 00:42:29.510 align:middle line:84%
and visualize something that
reminds me of those words

00:42:29.510 --> 00:42:35.180 align:middle line:84%
and aim it into those
areas, those energy centers.

00:42:35.180 --> 00:42:38.682 align:middle line:90%
So wise words.

00:42:38.682 --> 00:42:39.890 align:middle line:90%
There's a lot of great books.

00:42:39.890 --> 00:42:42.840 align:middle line:84%
So 10 ways I talk about in
terms of spiritual practice.

00:42:42.840 --> 00:42:43.640 align:middle line:90%
But you know what?

00:42:43.640 --> 00:42:44.440 align:middle line:90%
That's practice.

00:42:44.440 --> 00:42:45.680 align:middle line:90%
And that's important.

00:42:45.680 --> 00:42:47.810 align:middle line:90%
Practice is important.

00:42:47.810 --> 00:42:52.730 align:middle line:84%
But the real game for me,
spiritual wellness, and really

00:42:52.730 --> 00:42:57.090 align:middle line:84%
accessing spirit, is, how
am I showing up every day?

00:42:57.090 --> 00:43:00.640 align:middle line:84%
Am I smiling at people, or
am I frowning at people?

00:43:00.640 --> 00:43:05.700 align:middle line:10%
Am I encouraging people, or
am I discouraging people?

00:43:05.700 --> 00:43:09.450 align:middle line:10%
Am I forgiving people,
or am I holding grudges?

00:43:09.450 --> 00:43:12.630 align:middle line:84%
Am I asking for forgiveness,
or am I saying, eh.

00:43:12.630 --> 00:43:13.430 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:43:13.430 --> 00:43:15.420 align:middle line:84%
Maybe that was a bad
idea to blow them off.

00:43:15.420 --> 00:43:17.310 align:middle line:90%
So what?

00:43:17.310 --> 00:43:20.300 align:middle line:90%
Am I holding the door?

00:43:20.300 --> 00:43:22.800 align:middle line:84%
As I'm going through the door
and somebody's 10 feet behind,

00:43:22.800 --> 00:43:26.860 align:middle line:84%
am I holding it for them,
or am I letting it slam?

00:43:26.860 --> 00:43:30.370 align:middle line:84%
In my home, when I use the
last of the toilet paper,

00:43:30.370 --> 00:43:34.110 align:middle line:84%
am I replacing the roll, or
am I saying, let her do it?

00:43:34.110 --> 00:43:37.130 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there are a million
different things that

00:43:37.130 --> 00:43:39.780 align:middle line:90%
are what I call the real game.

00:43:39.780 --> 00:43:44.970 align:middle line:84%
And many of us have been talking
spiritual practice for 10 years

00:43:44.970 --> 00:43:45.770 align:middle line:90%
now.

00:43:45.770 --> 00:43:50.680 align:middle line:84%
So what I say is, how am
I showing up in the world?

00:43:50.680 --> 00:43:53.680 align:middle line:84%
Because the other, for
me, is just practice.

00:43:53.680 --> 00:43:58.840 align:middle line:84%
And if I save myself, and
I'm not really connected

00:43:58.840 --> 00:44:00.700 align:middle line:84%
with others and being
a beneficial presence

00:44:00.700 --> 00:44:05.170 align:middle line:84%
on the planet, then all
the practice, in my view,

00:44:05.170 --> 00:44:06.580 align:middle line:90%
is for naught.

00:44:06.580 --> 00:44:10.150 align:middle line:84%
I'll end by saying I wish
you all the very best

00:44:10.150 --> 00:44:13.650 align:middle line:84%
in winning in the
game of your life.

00:44:13.650 --> 00:44:17.410 align:middle line:84%
And on the trip, keep
things in perspective.

00:44:17.410 --> 00:44:19.810 align:middle line:90%
We know that life is messy.

00:44:19.810 --> 00:44:20.738 align:middle line:90%
It's challenging.

00:44:20.738 --> 00:44:22.780 align:middle line:84%
Scott Peck says in his
book "Road Less Traveled,"

00:44:22.780 --> 00:44:24.580 align:middle line:84%
first three words,
"Life is difficult."

00:44:24.580 --> 00:44:25.990 align:middle line:90%
So it is messy.

00:44:25.990 --> 00:44:28.370 align:middle line:84%
But if we keep things
in perspective,

00:44:28.370 --> 00:44:30.880 align:middle line:84%
keep these relationships, keep
our mission in perspective,

00:44:30.880 --> 00:44:32.440 align:middle line:90%
that can help.

00:44:32.440 --> 00:44:35.380 align:middle line:84%
And this message of keeping
things in perspective

00:44:35.380 --> 00:44:37.870 align:middle line:84%
is best illustrated
with a letter

00:44:37.870 --> 00:44:41.410 align:middle line:84%
that a young woman wrote
to her mom from college.

00:44:41.410 --> 00:44:44.200 align:middle line:84%
She says, dear
Mom, I thought I'd

00:44:44.200 --> 00:44:47.200 align:middle line:84%
write to let you know what's
been going on here at school.

00:44:47.200 --> 00:44:49.920 align:middle line:84%
Don't get worried, but
my arm's in a cast.

00:44:49.920 --> 00:44:52.480 align:middle line:84%
I broke it yesterday
when I did jump out

00:44:52.480 --> 00:44:55.240 align:middle line:84%
of the dorm window
because of the fire

00:44:55.240 --> 00:44:57.550 align:middle line:84%
which was accidentally
started when Mary and I got

00:44:57.550 --> 00:44:59.237 align:middle line:90%
too high smoking pot.

00:44:59.237 --> 00:45:01.522 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLING]

00:45:01.522 --> 00:45:03.350 align:middle line:90%


00:45:03.350 --> 00:45:05.575 align:middle line:90%
They kept us in jail overnight.

00:45:05.575 --> 00:45:07.450 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter it's
my writing hand that's

00:45:07.450 --> 00:45:09.760 align:middle line:84%
broken because I'm going
to quit school next week

00:45:09.760 --> 00:45:12.970 align:middle line:90%
and marry Johnny anyway.

00:45:12.970 --> 00:45:16.090 align:middle line:84%
Johnny's father has
offered him a partnership

00:45:16.090 --> 00:45:18.090 align:middle line:90%
in his gas station in Alaska.

00:45:18.090 --> 00:45:20.620 align:middle line:90%
That really sounds swell.

00:45:20.620 --> 00:45:22.750 align:middle line:84%
There's an extra room
over the station which

00:45:22.750 --> 00:45:25.240 align:middle line:84%
would be large enough at
least until the baby comes

00:45:25.240 --> 00:45:26.470 align:middle line:90%
in a few months.

00:45:26.470 --> 00:45:28.210 align:middle line:84%
Hope things are
going well for you.

00:45:28.210 --> 00:45:30.350 align:middle line:90%
Love, Molly.

00:45:30.350 --> 00:45:34.112 align:middle line:90%
PS, there's no fire.

00:45:34.112 --> 00:45:35.070 align:middle line:90%
I didn't break my hand.

00:45:35.070 --> 00:45:36.300 align:middle line:90%
I don't smoke dope.

00:45:36.300 --> 00:45:37.720 align:middle line:90%
I didn't get put in jail.

00:45:37.720 --> 00:45:39.610 align:middle line:90%
I didn't quit school.

00:45:39.610 --> 00:45:42.160 align:middle line:84%
I didn't marry Johnny,
and I'm not pregnant.

00:45:42.160 --> 00:45:44.025 align:middle line:84%
However, I did get
a D in chemistry,

00:45:44.025 --> 00:45:46.525 align:middle line:84%
and I just wanted you to put
things in a proper perspective.

00:45:46.525 --> 00:45:48.170 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLING]

00:45:48.170 --> 00:45:48.970 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:45:48.970 --> 00:45:50.822 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:45:50.822 --> 00:45:51.748 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:45:51.748 --> 00:45:54.483 align:middle line:90%


00:45:54.483 --> 00:45:56.150 align:middle line:84%
Keep things in their
proper perspective,

00:45:56.150 --> 00:45:58.377 align:middle line:84%
and I wish you all winning
in the game of your life.

00:45:58.377 --> 00:45:59.210 align:middle line:90%
Thank you very much.

00:45:59.210 --> 00:46:00.710 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:46:00.710 --> 00:46:05.810 align:middle line:90%


00:46:05.810 --> 00:46:08.560 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

